---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="ExCSV — CSV, but self-describing" wide>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <h1>CSV, but self-describing</h1>
      <p class="tagline">
        ExCSV adds inline schema, metadata, SQL companions, and aggregations to plain CSV.
        Zero dependencies. CLI-friendly. Backward-compatible.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="/spec/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the spec</a>
        <a href="/examples/" class="btn btn-secondary">See examples</a>
      </div>
      <p class="version-tag">v0.2 — Draft</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-code">
      <pre><code><span class="hl-meta">#!excsv version=0.2 delim=comma header=1 sql-dialect=postgres</span>
<span class="hl-meta">#@source: analytics_db.events</span>
<span class="hl-meta">#column name=date type=date</span>
<span class="hl-meta">#column name=event type=string</span>
<span class="hl-meta">#column name=count type=int</span>
<span class="hl-meta">#$ddl: CREATE TABLE events (date DATE, event TEXT, count INTEGER)</span>
<span class="hl-meta">#%sum: ,,1250</span>
date,event,count
2026-01-15,signup,320
2026-01-15,purchase,180
2026-01-16,signup,410
2026-01-16,purchase,340</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features -->
  <section class="features">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Schema annotations</h3>
      <p>Define column types, constraints, defaults, and validation patterns right inside the file. No sidecar schema needed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Built-in aggregations</h3>
      <p>Embed sum, avg, count, min/max, and more as metadata rows. Consumers get stats without scanning the data.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>SQL companions</h3>
      <p>Ship DDL and DQL alongside data, tagged per dialect (<code>mysql</code>, <code>postgres</code>, <code>clickhouse</code>...). Recreate the schema in any database.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>CLI-friendly</h3>
      <p>All metadata lines start with <code>#</code>, so <code>grep</code>, <code>awk</code>, <code>head</code>, and <code>cut</code> work on the data section out of the box.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Zipped distribution</h3>
      <p><code>.excsv.zip</code> archives carry their summary in the ZIP comment — read schema and aggregations without unzipping. No extraction needed for preview.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Backward-compatible</h3>
      <p>Any CSV reader can consume the data section. Metadata lines are comments. Nothing breaks.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why -->
  <section class="why">
    <h2>Why ExCSV?</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4>Progressive enhancement</h4>
        <p>Start with plain CSV. Add a header line. Add column types when you need them. Add aggregations or SQL when you want them. Every layer is optional.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>No JSON required</h4>
        <p>Metadata is line-oriented key-value, not a nested structure. Easy to read, easy to write, easy to diff.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Multi-dialect SQL</h4>
        <p>One file can ship MySQL, PostgreSQL, and ClickHouse DDL side-by-side. Pick the right flavor when you load the data into a database.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Self-describing files</h4>
        <p>The file carries its own schema, provenance, and statistics. No external metadata files, no guessing column types.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Prior art -->
  <section class="inspired-by">
    <h2>Inspired by</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4><a href="https://docs.astropy.org/en/stable/io/ascii/ecsv.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ECSV</a> — Astropy's Enhanced Character-Separated Values</h4>
        <p>Showed that a CSV file can carry a versioned signature, per-column schema, and table-level metadata as <code>#</code>-prefixed lines and still round-trip through every plain CSV reader. ExCSV adopts the same shape but trades nested YAML for line-oriented <code>key=value</code> pairs — friendlier to <code>grep</code>, <code>diff</code>, and humans.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4><a href="https://docs.influxdata.com/influxdb/v2/reference/syntax/annotated-csv/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Annotated CSV</a> — InfluxDB</h4>
        <p>Established the "one annotation row, one value per data column" pattern with <code>#datatype</code>, <code>#group</code>, and <code>#default</code> rows. ExCSV's <code>#%</code> aggregation rows (<code>sum</code>, <code>avg</code>, <code>min</code>, ...) inherit this layout directly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="full-credit">Full credit and a translation guide on the <a href="/spec/#prior-art">specification</a>.</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }
  .tagline {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .version-tag {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.6em 1.4em;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }
  .btn:hover { text-decoration: none; opacity: 0.85; }
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
  }
  .btn-secondary {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .hero-code pre {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .features {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .card {
    background: var(--color-card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .card p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .why {
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .why h2 {
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .grid-2 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .grid-2 h4 { margin-top: 0; }
  .grid-2 h4 a {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .grid-2 h4 a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .grid-2 p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .inspired-by {
    padding: 1rem 0 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .inspired-by h2 {
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .full-credit {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
      padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
    }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
    .features { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
